article.headline: Drake 74, Northern Iowa 61
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Klayton Korver scored a career-high 23 points, freshman Josh Young added 15 and Drake beat Northern Iowa 74-61 Saturday to snap a two-game losing streak. Korver was 6-of-10 from 3-point range to lead Drake (12-10, 3-8 MVC), which beat Northern Iowa for just the third time in its last 13 tries. After trailing most of the first half, the Bulldogs took the lead for good with an 8-0 run to start the second half. Young and Korver hit 3's to cap the run, which put the Bulldogs ahead 42-37. Young then split Northern Iowa's post defense for a layup that pushed Drake's lead to seven, 49-42. Ajay Calvin followed with back-to-back jumpers and a 3 to give the Bulldogs a nine-point lead midway through the second half. Young buried a three to push Drake's lead to 61-51 with 6:48 left. Northern Iowa crept back within 61-55, but Korver answered with a 3 that bounced off the rim, hit the backboard and dropped through. Al Stewart followed with a layup, and Korver's sixth 3-pointer of the game -- a 25-footer at the shot clock buzzer -- put the Bulldogs ahead 69-55. Eric Coleman scored 15 points and grabbed 14 rebounds for Northern Iowa (15-6, 6-4), which missed 12 of its final 14 attempts from 3-point range. Travis Brown and Brooks McKowen each had 11 for the Panthers. Northern Iowa hit five of its first eight 3-point tries, but Korver's three at the first-half buzzer brought Drake within 35-34 at the break. Calvin scored 13 points and Stewart chipped in with 12 for Drake. The win gave the Bulldogs a 3-0 record against in-state rivals Iowa, Iowa State and Northern Iowa this season.
